Amani National Congress leader Musalia Mudavadi's family is in mourning following the death of his mother, Hannah Atsianzale. The former vice-president made the announcement through a Twitter post noting that the 92-year-old died at Nairobi hospital on Monday morning. "As a family, we are devastated by this loss but are bearing it with grace. Please remember us in your prayers. The Lord gives and the Lord takes. May our dear Mum's soul RIP," Mudavadi said. More to follow...